<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="346" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,1209,1451]" pageId="45" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1317,1343]" pageId="45" pageNumber="346">Remarks.</emphasis>
These two sclerites may not belong to the same species. The internal mould of the cranidium shows evidence of carrying raised transverse ridges anteriorly which may have been strong on the dorsal surface. The same feature is seen on 
<taxonomicName box="[353,503,1389,1416]" class="Trilobita" family="Illaenidae" genus="Illaenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Corynexochida" pageId="45" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undefined-3">
<emphasis box="[353,443,1389,1415]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="346">Illaenus</emphasis>
sp. 3
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[570,659,1390,1416]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="45" pageNumber="346">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, but not enough is known of either species to prove they are the same species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
